<br>
I have a similar question on resists.  Is there a 'magic' level (i.e. 100) that is a minimum before it makes a difference when cast upon?  Does anyone know how the calculation to resist goes?  i.e. 69&lt;resist stat&lt;80 then resist chance is 50%.  Is there a level that you make 90% chance to resist, and yes you can get higher resist, but not really worth it? Like this chart (all made up numbers):<br>
Resist stat       chance to resist spell<br>
50-59              40%<br>
60-69              55%<br>
70-84              70%<br>
85-99              80%<br>
100-110           90%<br>
111-119           91%<br>
120-149           93%<br>
(and so on)  You get the point, a non-linear progression.<br>
<br>
I know there is a level factor to the 'chance to resist' calculation.  If you know that also, then great.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Answers, I want answers!!  hehe<br>
<br>
Mappill <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uligge.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ligge</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_ball.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(8/22/01 11:44:17 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.eqguide.com/images/vermsmall.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 'Key' levels of AC and resist? Formulas to Calculate dam</span><hr size=1> I dont think you can get a definitive answer on the resists issue. Level of the MoB vs your level matters a ton too there.<br>
<br>
At 50-52 I needed 140+ MR (I tended to pull at 155ish mr) to safely pull Fear - meaning I resisted 90% or higher. Now I probably have just as much success at 120s.<br>
<br>
As far as the AC issue goes, I cant 100% confirm but from personal experience and nonscientic testing methods - ie. no guarrantee level of a MoB I pulled over and over again. However they were all gnolls and they were all blue. I did some some testing with my enchanter while soloing at 520ish vs 549 vs 552 AC and the damage mitigation/chance of living, how often the fights were close etc etc etc results showed there was a very apparent difference for me once I crossed the 550 mark. Whereas the 520 vs 549 didnt make much difference.  I also did this at 496 vs 505 AC when I was a little younger and fighting other blues and came to the same belief that whoever came up with the scaling of 50 was probably pretty correct. <p><p align=left><font face="Trebuchet MS, Tahoma" size="1"><a href=http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=6031>Ligge</a> - Changing Tide CoGuildleader<br><font color=green><a href="http://pub17.ezboard.com/beqguide">Changing Tide's Boards</a><b> || </b><a href="http://pub2.ezboard.com/bthefolk">The Folk's Boards</a></font><br><img src=http://www.eqguide.com/changingtide/images/inpom.jpg><br><b>"You must be the change you wish to see in the world." - Mahatma Ghandi</b><br>"Never argue with an idiot. They drag you down to their level then beat you with experience."</font></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon2.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukalinn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kalinn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(8/23/01 8:40:01 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://members.home.net/azurecrayon/wolf.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 'Key' levels of AC and resist? Formulas to Calculate dam</span><hr size=1> definately on way to be positive on your resists and how much you will resist.  basically the higher your resist, the higher the chance you will resist is, but its still just a chance and not definite.  you could have 250 RM and still get feared or rooted, however having such a high resist means your chance of resisting is much higher than someone with a resist of 50.  there is also the partial resists when it comes to nukes, and the higher your resist is, the higher the chance you get a partial resist and not full damage.  and yes, level vs your target matters a great deal, as does the target themselves.  some fears are stronger than others, some ae's are stronger than others.<br>
<br>
im not sure on the ac issue whether its a 50ac step system or not.  i imagine its like some of the stats where there are &quot;magic numbers&quot; that give more benefit than other levels. <p>-K<br>
