<br>
For example Lendinara the Keeper casts an unresistable AOE for 400dd.  Ditto Flame Song of Ro of the Chardok Queen for around 600 per tick.<br>
<br>
TOV trash aoe is easily resisted by a level 60 with 180ish resists.  The same trash will completely own a level 50 with 180s resists.<br>
<br>
Nagafen's aoe is easily resisted by a level 50 with 140MR/FR<br>
<br>
Trakanons AoE will tend to hit level 60s until they get close to 255PR at which point they become immune to the dot.<br>
<br>
Basically the point is that there are no hard and fast rules about resists - resists are situational.  That being said dont expect any resist to do anything meaningful under 100 unbuffed. <p><b>Sashanna Bluueheeler</b><BR><b>Hierophant of The Companions</b></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udreth1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dreth1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(8/29/01 6:28:02 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 'Key' levels of AC and resist? Formulas to Calculate dam</span><hr size=1> Resists are funny though, and Verant has stated that &quot;dragon class&quot; spells/effects are different than normal effects/spells when determining.<br>
